<div class="blog-faq">
<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>Is gynecomastia surgery painful?</h3>
<p>Most patients report mild to moderate discomfort after gynecomastia surgery, which is well-managed with prescribed pain medications. The discomfort typically peaks within the first 48 to 72 hours and diminishes steadily. Wearing a compression garment as directed helps reduce swelling and discomfort.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>How long after a hair transplant will I see results?</h3>
<p>Transplanted hair begins to grow within 3 to 4 months after the procedure. Significant improvement is typically visible by 6 to 9 months, with full results achieved at 12 to 18 months. The transplanted hair is permanent and grows naturally.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>Can men have a facelift without looking feminine?</h3>
<p>Yes, a skilled surgeon tailors the facelift technique specifically for male patients, maintaining masculine features such as the jawline and brow position. Dr. Manoj K Johar has extensive experience performing male facelifts that produce natural, masculine results.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>What is the best age for male plastic surgery?</h3>
<p>There is no single best age, as it depends on the procedure and the patient's goals. Gynecomastia surgery can be performed once breast development is complete, typically after age 16 to 18. Facial rejuvenation procedures are common in the 40s and beyond. The best time is when you have a specific concern that can be addressed surgically.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>Will liposuction scars be visible?</h3>
<p>Liposuction incisions are very small, typically 3 to 5 millimeters, and are placed in inconspicuous locations. Over time, these scars fade significantly and are usually barely noticeable. Your surgeon will discuss incision placement during your consultation.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>How do I prepare for male plastic surgery?</h3>
<p>Preparation includes maintaining a stable weight, quitting smoking at least 4 to 6 weeks before surgery, avoiding certain medications and supplements, eating a nutritious diet, and arranging for post-operative support. Detailed instructions will be provided during your consultation at Dr. Johar's clinic.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>Are the results of male plastic surgery permanent?</h3>
<p>Results from most male plastic surgery procedures are long-lasting, especially when combined with a healthy lifestyle. Gynecomastia results are typically permanent, as are rhinoplasty and hair transplant results. Aging will continue, but the improvements achieved through surgery are maintained over the long term.</p>
</div>
</div>

